The Rehearsal Studio~
   The underbelly of the theatre isn't nearly the seedy den of iniquity one
might expect.  Being built below the crenelations of Festival Street however,
just beyond the walls is the open sky, allowing natural light in the lower
level through small windows.  It's not exactly bright, but it's not impossible
to see either.  The rehearsal studio takes up most of the lower level.  The
floor is sprung wood, ideal for dancing.  Floor to ceiling mirrors cover one
wall making it easy for an actor to see what they might look like from the
audience.  Props, scenery, and costumes are stored in various places down here,
certainly home to more than a few rats.  At the far end of the room serves as
the business office for the Leading Player, leader of the troupe.~
